## Why This Is Asked
Tests the ability to design a real-time, dropout-tolerant ICA pipeline for mobile sensor arrays, a common edge case in vehicles. It probes the candidate’s stance on online whitening with missing channels, cadence trade-offs, algorithm selection under partial data, permutation handling across bands, failure detection, and practical evaluation with groundtruth.

## Key Concepts
- Dropout-tolerant whitening
- Online demixing cadences
- Per-bin ICA vs joint diagonalization under partial observability
- Cross-bin permutation alignment with missing data
- Failure detection and reinitialization
- On-device evaluation with ground-truth sources

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo online whitening resilient to missing channels
function updateWhitening(X, mask) {
  // X: channels x frames
  // mask: 1 if channel present, 0 if dropped
  const Xpresent = X.filter((row, idx) => mask[idx] === 1);
  const cov = computeCovariance(Xpresent);
  // add small jitter to diagonal for stability
  const W = inverseSqrt(cov + eps * I);
  return W;
}
```

